      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic model with frictional contact captures dominant load-transfer mechanisms; sensitivity analysis confirms negligible contribution of omitted thread geometry.",
      "rationale": "The continuum representation of screw threads was justified by a sensitivity study showing less than 2% QoI change versus a detailed thread model. Frictional contact (mu=0.3) between screw and vertebral body surrogate was validated against published literature. Model form is appropriate for the COU."
