      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the COU decision variables and to clinical failure modes identified in the risk analysis.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the spine; yield force is the primary structural integrity indicator; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to fatigue life prediction. All three QoIs are explicitly referenced in the 510(k) substantial equivalence argument. Relevance is established."
