    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) reflects the standardized single-configuration nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol and is judged acceptable given the tight QoI agreement (all E/uval < 1.0) and the direct relevance of the validation scenario to the COU. The FEA modeling framework is deemed credible for supporting the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw.",
